-- Nigeria Leads Greece 1-0 in First Half of World Cup Game on Kalu Uche Goal
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-17T14:31:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/nigeria-leads-greece-1-0-in-first-half-of-world-cup-game-on-kalu-uche-goal.html

          
          
             Nigeria leads Greece 1-0 after 30
minutes of their World Cup Group B game in Bloemfontein, South
Africa. Kalu Uche scored with a free kick in the 15th minute.  
 Gonzalo Higuain scored three goals as Argentina beat South
Korea 4-1 earlier to move atop Group B. France and Mexico player
in Group A later today.  
          
          


  


        